history.content:
Email sishelp@berkeley.edu, they can generally re-enroll you without needing to drop the class or anything. It is a quirk of the swap function, which may have to do with making sure you manually select the *other* sections you are already enrolled in, as well as the ones you are trying to get into (trying to change from DIS1 to DIS2? Select DIS2, but also select LAB1 and LEC1 to be safe).

--------------------

I had a similar error with CS61B where I was originally enrolled in lec, lab, and dis, did a swap, and ended up in only a lec and a dis (I'm guessing a bug with cal central). When I tried to swap again, I was unable to since I wasn't enrolled in a lab! I had to drop CS61B and reinroll to get back into the class. I would submit a ticket and email your counselor.

This is not possible. If you were moved to the waitlist because you tried changing to a full lab, then you were moved to the waitlist for the class as a whole (including lecture and discussion as well). If you were processed off of the waitlist after that, you would have gotten in all three components.

children.subject: You aren't even waitlisted for the lab? That sounds like a bug in the system.
Did anyone ever figure out whats going on? I have a similar problem.

I switched from an open lab to an open lab. But when I clicked the confirm button to swap only the labs, the swap was unsuccessful and resulted in me not getting into the other lab, whilst being dropped from the one I was already enrolled in. But I am not on the wait list. I am still enrolled in Lecture and Discussion.

This is definitely a bug. I had a similar issue a few weeks ago in which I was dropped from the lecture but still in the lab and discussion. SIS resolved the issue for me - email sishelp@berkeley.edu and they should be able to fix it. Good luck!

Yep, just email sishelp@berkeley.edu

"When you attempted to switch your discussion sections you did not first select all of the related class components for which you are enrolled; you only chose a new discussion section which unfortunately de-enrolled you from a discussion section when your transaction was processed. When you edit your enrolled class options (i.e. switch lab/discussion section, change grading option, etc.), you must first choose all of the related class components for which you are enrolled in to proceed."

Even though the related class components show up as being automatically selected in the UI on my end... But either way, they enrolled me back in no problem  :)
Same happened to me, trying to swap discussions into an open/no waitlist discussion. Emailed SIShelp and will update when I hear back.

This occurred when I tried swapping lab sections from friday to wednesday (back then I was enrolled in Friday lab), and it resulted in me being dropped from the lab I was already enrolled in and now I am no longer in a lab.
